to mob AI, and how they'll chose spells more wisely, but not the nature of the resistance changes.<br>
<br>
So, what exactly did they do to resistences? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zukobim>Zukobim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/9/03 12:05:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3002.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Resistance Changes</span><hr size=1> Generally SOE made NPC's spell casting rules more like the PC spell casting rules.<br>
They also made resists more usefull compared to levels, so a lower level PC would good resists can resists as if he was higher in level, but with worse resists.<br>
<br>
Previously NPC would get one unresistable spell cast on you regardless of level, which made chanters very nasty, because they tried to mezz or charm you. Now all NPC spells are checked against the same resist rules as with PCs.<br>
<br>
NPCs also had a tendency to cast to the same few spells again and on the wrong targets. This made some funny situations where a necro would get slowed 10+ times during a battle, because his pet would be meleeing, but he would be the main agro dealer.<br>
<br>
NPCs can still cast without line-of-sight and still land spell on you, if you are out of range of the actually spell, as far as I know.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cily>Cily</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/9/03 2:56:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3002.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jnaggy291392mi/EQ/bubbles1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Resistance Changes</span><hr size=1> You can out run NPC spells now, and they wont innitiate a spell if you are not in LoS (too bad most new zones seem to ignore LoS tho).<br>
<br>
As for resists, the change I really notice is that every damn MOB, even low level raid crap in LoY is either unresistable or has a lure type check. Getting old fast. Resists are becoming next to useless in raid encounters until you have 400+ or so. /sigh<br>
<br>
Cily <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zukobim>Zukobim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/9/03 3:45:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3002.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Resistance Changes</span><hr size=1> I especially noticed the change when I was hunting Sirens in CS for shawl quest drops.<br>
<br>
Before the change my team (55 druid, 57 cleric and 60 warrior) would get mezzed, nuked and charmed all the time, because their first spell cast was unresistable.<br>
A charmed warrior and a mezzed druid can really make things ugly fast.<br>
<br>
After the change I can solo the Sirens with my 60 warrior without any problems and with the same gear as before.<br>
Only spell that is hitting me is the tash line.<br>
The rest of the spells they cast are either resisted by the 100MR or by the fact that I am level 60 and they are like level 37. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wubaogoldenarmz>Wubao Goldenarmz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 452<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/9/03 6:20:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3002.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Pre-PoP</span><hr size=1> Prior to the release of Planes of Power, SOE tweaked the resistance tables, meaning you needed much higher in some cases, to only slightly higher in other cases, resistance in order to have the same effectiveness you had before.<br>
<br>
In other words, running around with 101 MR PRE-Resist changes usually meant that goblins in Sol A weren't gonna land CRAP on you. And of course their spell selection was horrible, so that if ever they did land a spell on you it was a silly little 80 point nuke.<br>
<br>
Well they changed all that. Now goblins are nuking for 250 and without pretty damn good resists, they're landing them a lot more frequently than before.<br>
<br>
GREEN CON goblins.<br>
<br>
That's nothing compared to dark blue cons or higher, who are now landing some very meaty spells, like necro mobs now stack dots on you and wizards now ice comet you.<br>
<br>
This drastically affects PULLERS (nothing like getting rooted and nuked dead by a light blue frog in Seb, yay!).<br>
<br>
They made these changes FOR PoP however, because of the increase in levels and increase in level of encounter, they needed to make a newer top end to the resist tables.<br>
<br>
The side effect is that this change affected all classes, all levels top to bottom. Where this really REALLY sucks is the LOW END game, where RESIST gear typically does not exist (the occasional Blackened Alloy Coif or Runed Bone Fork aside, most level 30 toons aren't running around with 100 in all resists unbuffed).<br>
<br>
Kinda stupid if you ask me.<br>
<br>
And part of the reason that SOME zones are even more deserted than before (Sol A. without some serious backup is a death trap ... Dalnir's with all those Kly just isn't worth thinking about anymore) for people who are LEVEL appropriate to those zones.<br>
<br>
Silly SOE. Making changes and not thinking about the side effects. <br>
<br>
Hope that adds some perspective you were looking for. This change was instituted in a patch a few months before Planes of Power was released. It was before the monk defense change/manaburn/modrod/CH nerf patch. It was even before the XP table tweak patch. It's a pretty old patch now that I think about it.<br>
